* Introduction

   ruby-libnet is a Ruby binding for libnet library written in C
   programming language. 

   libnet homepage: http://packetfactory.net/libnet/

* Homepage
   
   http://ruby-libnet.rubyforge.org

* Requirements
   
   Ruby (Tested on 1.8.x)

* Source

   svn checkout svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/ruby-libnet

* Compile
   If ruby supports dynamic link of extension module on your OS,
   following commands will install ruby-libnet:

   ruby extconf.rb
   make
   make install

* Usage

   See the documentation under the directory 'doc'.
   Directory 'tests' contains some simple scripts.

* Bug Reports

